Soobum Im/USA TODAY SportsLaMarcus Aldridge and the Trail Blazers and Tim Duncan and the Spurs split the season series. Insider offers a breakdown of every playoff series using an expert combination of scouting from Amin Elhassan and advanced metrics from Bradford Doolittle to answer three crucial questions. Also included are predictions from the writers and the classic Log5 formula for determining matchup probabilities. Raise your hand if you thought the quickest Western Conference first-round series would be won by the Portland Trail Blazers. If you raised your hand, call your mother and admit to her that you're a liar. The Blazers managed to evade the seven-game sentence every other advancing Western Conference playoff team had to fulfill, despite being the only lower seed to prevail. Now they face an even more monumental Texas challenge in the San Antonio Spurs, the defending Western Conference champs and owners of the best regular-season record in the NBA. The teams split the season series, with Portland winning the first two meetings (including a win at San Antonio), while the Spurs captured the last two (including a victory at Portland). Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs Western Conference playoffs Semifinal preview To read more of Insider's scouting report of the Trail Blazers-Spurs playoff series, become an Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits Â» Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Amin Elhassan Follow Archive Video coordinator, college scout, Phoenix Suns Assistant director of basketball operations, Phoenix Suns MBA from Arizona State University Bradford Doolittle Follow Archive Sports reporter, Kansas City Star, 2002-09 Writer, Baseball, Baseball Prospectus Co-author, Pro Basketball Prospectus Member, Baseball Writers Association of America Member, Professional Basketball Writers Association